ActAccessible Canada Act
SubjectOrder Designating the Minister of State (Diversity, Inclusion and Persons with Disabilities) as the Minister for the Purposes of the Accessible Canada Act
PrecisOrder (1) repealing Order in Council P.C. 2019-1043 of July 9, 2019; and (2) designating the Minister of State (Diversity, Inclusion and Persons with Disabilities), a member of the King's Privy Council for Canada, as the Minister for the Purposes of the ACCESSIBLE CANADA ACT.
